<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870702-0138 </DOCNO><HL> McDonnell Unit GetsTotal $416.3 MillionIn Navy Contracts</HL><DD> 07/02/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MD TXT LK ITT CDA UIS GE UTX TRRAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   McDonnell Aircraft Co., a unit of McDonnell Douglas Corp., received Navy contracts totaling $416.3 million for production of AV-8B aircraft and FA-18 aircraft support equipment.    Textron Inc. won a $186.9 million Navy contract for landing-craft vehicles. Lockheed Shipbuilding Co., a unit of Lockheed Corp., also was issued a $115.6 million Navy contract for landing-craft vehicles.    ITT Corp. received a $46.9 million Air Force contract for missile warning-system support services.    Control Data Corp. got a $27.7 million Navy contract for aircraft computer equipment.    Unisys Corp. was issued a $26.9 million Air Force contract for electronic equipment.    Units of General Electric Co. won contracts totaling $26.3 million for base-support services for the Army, aircraft-engine development for the Air Force, and aircraft-navigation equipment for the Navy.    Units of United Technologies Corp. were awarded contracts totaling $17.5 million for aircraft-engine development for the Air Force and SH-60B helicopter equipment for the Navy.    Tracor Inc. received a $15.2 million Navy contract for engineering services. </TEXT></DOC>